---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 230
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Happy Death
  - 959
By: Ibn Sa'ad
---
Umm Aiman was seen in tears and was asked if she was weeping for the
death of the Prophet. She replied： ‘Not for him do I weep. Know I not
that he hath gone to that which is better for him than this world? But
I weep for the tidings of heaven (akhbâru 's-samâ) that have been cut
off from us.‘
